row, T., A. Wistuba & P. Harbarth 2005. [http://www.carnivorousplants.org/cpn/Species/v34n1p4_6.html ''Heliamphora sarracenioides'', a new species of ''Heliamphora'' (Sarraceniaceae) from Venezuela]. ''[[Carnivorous Plant Newsletter]]'' '''34'''(1): 4\u20136.</ref> || 2005 || || [[Venezuela]] || 2400\u20132450 m\n|-\n| ''[[Heliamphora tatei]]'' || [[Henry Gleason|Gleason]]<ref name=Gleason /> || 1931 || [[File:Heliamphora tatei.JPG|80px]] || [[Venezuela]] || 1700\u20132400 m\n|-\n| ''[[Heliamphora uncinata]]'' || [[Joachim Nerz|Nerz]], [[Andreas Wistuba|Wistuba]] & [[Andreas Fleischmann|A.Fleischm.]]<ref name=three /> || 2009 || || [[Venezuela]] || 1850 m\n|}\n\n===Incompletely diagnosed taxa===\nA further two [[undescribed taxon|incompletely diagnosed taxa]] are known that may represent distinct species in their own right.<ref name=McPherson2011 />\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n! Species !! Distribution !! Altitudinal distribution\n|-\n| [[Heliamphora sp. 'Akop\u00e1n Tepui'|''Heliamphora'' sp. 'Akop\u00e1n Tepui']] || [[Venezuela]] || 1800\u20131900 m\n|-\n| [[Heliamphora sp. 'Angasima Tepui'|''Heliamphora'' sp. 'Angasima Tepui']] || [[Venezuela]] || 2200\u20132250 m\n|}\n\n===Varieties===\nTwo [[Variety (botany)|varieties]] are currently recognised in the genus: [[Heliamphora minor|''H.&nbsp;minor'' var. ''pilosa'']] and the [[Autonym (botany)|autonymous]] [[Heliamphora minor|''H.&nbsp;minor'' var. ''minor'']].<ref>{{in lang|es}} Fleischmann, A. & J.R. Grande Allende 2012 ['2011']. [https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/862/86222271001.pdf Taxonom\u00eda de ''Heliamphora minor'' Gleason (Sarraceniaceae) del Auy\u00e1n-tepui, incluyendo una nueva variedad]. [Taxonomy of ''Heliamphora minor'' Gleason (Sarraceniaceae) from Auy\u00e1n-tepui, including a new variety.] ''Acta Bot\u00e1nica Venezuelica'' '''34'''(1): 1\u201311.</ref> Additionally, an [[undescribed taxon|undescribed]] variant of ''[[Heliamphora pulchella|H.&nbsp;pulchella]]'' lacking long retentive hairs is known from [[Amur\u00ed Tepui]].<ref name=McPherson2011 />\n\n===Cultivars===\nThe only registered cultivar is [[Heliamphora 'Red Mambo'|''Heliamphora'' 'Red Mambo']] by Francois Boulianne from Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://legacy.carnivorousplants.org/cpn/Species/v45n4p158_163.html|title=Cps cultivar|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Natural hybrids==\nAt least eleven [[natural hybrid]]s have been recorded:<ref name=McPherson2011 />\n\n*''[[Heliamphora arenicola|H. arenicola]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora ionasi|H. ionasi]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora ceracea|H. ceracea]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora hispida|H. hispida]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora chimantensis|H. chimantensis]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora pulchella|H. pulchella]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora elongata|H. elongata]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora ionasi|H. ionasi]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora exappendiculata|H. exappendiculata]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora huberi|H. huberi]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora exappendiculata|H. exappendiculata]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora pulchella|H. pulchella]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora glabra|H. glabra]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora nutans|H. nutans]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora huberi|H. huberi]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora pulchella|H. pulchella]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora neblinae|H. neblinae]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora parva|H. parva]]''\n*''[[Heliamphora purpurascens|H. purpurascens]]'' \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora sarracenioides|H. sarracenioides]]''\n*[[Heliamphora sp. 'Akop\u00e1n Tepui'|''H.'' sp. 'Akop\u00e1n Tepui']] \u00d7 ''[[Heliamphora pulchella|H. pulchella]]''\n\nAdditionally, putative complex hybrids occur on the [[Neblina Massif]] among populations of ''[[Heliamphora ceracea|H. ceracea]]'', ''[[Heliamphora hispida|H. hispida]]'', ''[[Heliamphora neblinae|H. neblinae]]'', and ''[[Heliamphora parva|H. parva]]''.<ref name=McPherson2011 /> Putative crosses between ''H.&nbsp;macdonaldae'' and ''H.&nbsp;tatei'' have also been recorded in the southern part of [[Cerro Duida]].<ref>Rivadavia, F. (2008). [http://www.cpukforum.com/forum/index.php?showtopic=27408 Cerro Duida, Cerro Avispa, Cerro Aracamuni] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20140414180324/http://www.cpukforum.com/forum/index.php?showtopic=27408 |date=2014-04-14 }}. CPUK Forum, 14 June 2008.</ref>\n\n== Diversification ==\nClosely related species tend to be geographically closely distributed. Major ''Heliamphora'' clades probably emerged through both vicariance and dispersal during Miocene with more recent diversification driven by vertical displacement during the Pleistocene glacial-interglacial thermal oscillations.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Liu|first=Sukuan|last2=Smith|first2=Stacey D.|date=2020-04-30|title=Phylogeny and Biogeography of South American Marsh Pitcher Plant Genus Heliamphora (Sarraceniaceae) Endemic to the Guiana Highlands|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.04.29.068395v1|journal=bioRxiv|language=en|pages=2020.04.29.068395|doi=10.1101/2020.04.29.068395}}</ref> \n<br />\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin|2}}\n* Barnes, B. 2010. [http://www.carnivorousplants.org/cpn/articles/CPNv39n1p26_27.pdf Growing ''Heliamphora'' indoors year-round.] ''[[Carnivorous Plant Newsletter]]'' '''39'''(1): 26\u201327.\n* Baumgartl, W. 1993. [http://www.carnivorousplants.org/cpn/articles/CPNv22n4p86_92.pdf The genus ''Heliamphora''.] ''[[Carnivorous Plant Newsletter]]'' '''22'''(4): 86\u201392.\n* Brittnacher, J. 2013. Phylogeny and biogeography of the Sarraceniaceae. ''[[Carnivorous Plant Newsletter]]'' '''42'''(3): 99\u2013106.\n* B\u00fctschi, L. [translation by D. Huber & K. Ammann] 1989. [http://www.carnivorousplants.org/cpn/articles/CPNv18n2p47_51.pdf Carnivorous plants of Auyantepui in Venezuela. Part 2.] ''[[Carnivorous Plant Newsletter]]'' '''18'''(2): 47\u201351.\n* Clemmens, N.J. 2010. [https://web.archive.org/web/20120325043336/http://www.auscps.com/Newsletters/Carniflora%20News%20vol%201%20No%203.pdf ''Heliamphora'' cultivation.] ''[[Carniflora News]]'' '''1'''(3): 12\u201313.